|
ğŸ”¸ **B-9. Grouping Etiquette**:|  
|â¤ Invite to groups before engaging in conflicts. Random invites or invites during active hunts or contests are not acceptable.|
|
|
|
ğŸ”¸ **B-10. Prevention of Body Access**:|  
|Engaging in actions to deliberately prevent others from accessing a defeated body is forbidden. Actions include:|
|
â¤ Intentionally expiring within food sources, causing a blockage to the consumption action.|
â¤ Choosing to bleed out in places difficult to access, such as elevated terrains, waters, or constricted caves.|
â¤ Self-drowning with the aim to deter others from feeding on the body.|
â¤ Voluntarily leaping off cliffs. However, scenarios like being naturally killed in water or utilizing water as a defensive strategy are exempted.|
|
|
|
ğŸ”¸ **B-11. Combat Halts on Casualty**:|  
â¤ If a combat situation results in a body dropping, the fight must immediately cease.|
